Title: Refactor uv invocations to use --env-file (CLAUDE_ENV_FILE leak fix)
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-30
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-30T16:35Z claude created — see AEDIST commit 4000c21 for the model fix

--- body ---
## Context

Discovery 2026-04-30: Claude Code's `~/.claude/scripts/on-start.sh` was
appending all `~/.claude/.env` keys into `$CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`. Claude Code
inlines that file's contents as `KEY=value` prefix in every spawned
`bash -c` command line — making secrets visible to anyone running
`ps -ef` on the host. An accidental `ps -ef` during AEDIST work leaked
the entire key set into a chat transcript; keys had to be rotated.

User-side fix (committed in `~/.claude/scripts/on-start.sh`): the hook
no longer persists `.env` into `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`. Tools that need keys
must source `.env` explicitly.

## Project-specific work

The top-level Makefile has 1 `uv run` invocation. Minimal refactor:

1. If/when the call needs an API key, change to
   `uv run --env-file .env ...`.
2. Drop any `export KEY := $(shell grep ...)` patterns referencing
   secrets.
3. Add a Makefile header comment naming project `.env` as the canonical
   env source.

If the single uv invocation does not require any secret today, this
ticket is mostly preventive — the next uv-call to add will benefit
from the convention being in place.

## Reference

AEDIST `experiments/Makefile` (commit `4000c21`) shows the model
pattern: a single `UV_RUN := uv run --project .. --env-file ../.env`
macro, with a header block documenting the env policy.

## Test

After refactor:
```bash
ps -ef | grep '<the uv child>' | grep -E '[A-Z_]+=[^[:space:]]+'
```
No `KEY=value` pairs should appear.

## Exit criteria

- The uv invocation routes through `--env-file` (or a `$(UV_RUN)` macro
  if more invocations land later).
- No `export KEY := $(shell ...)` patterns referencing secrets.
- Project .env declared as canonical source in a Makefile header
  comment.
